  "bio_raw": "Farabe Khan Alif is a statistician and academic specializing in applied and computational statistics. He completed his Master’s by Research at Universiti Putra Malaysia, where his work focused on extreme value theory, automated threshold selection for the Generalized Pareto Distribution, and applications to hydrological, financial, and public health datasets. His research has been presented at international conferences. He is currently a Lecturer in his early career at the University of Liberal Arts Bangladesh, teaching statistics- and mathematics-focused courses, while actively pursuing research in extreme value analysis, environmental statistics, and biostatistics.",
  "stated_interests": [
    "Statistics, Extreme Value Statistics, Generalized Pareto Distribution, Generalized Extreme Value, Business Statistics, Environmental Statistics, Medical Statistica, Medical Extreme Value Application."
  ],
  "education": [
    {
      "raw": "Education\nMSc\nin Applied and Computation Statistics from Universiti Putra Malaysia (UPM), 2025.\nBSc\n(With Honors) in Statistics from Jahangirnagar University, 2023."
    }
  ],
